article.description: Mike Holloway was 10 of 10 from the field for 21 points, Marques Townes added 18 and Fairleigh Dickinson won its home opener 111-70 over Division-III Fairleigh Dickinson-Florham on Monday night.
article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson beats FDU-Florham 111-70
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. -- Mike Holloway was 10 of 10 from the field for 21 points, Marques Townes added 18 and Fairleigh Dickinson won its home opener 111-70 over Division-III Fairleigh Dickinson-Florham on Monday night. The 111 points were the Knights' most in a regulation game since scoring 112 in a win against Saint Francis U. on Feb. 16, 1984. Earl Potts Jr. added 14 points and 11 rebounds for Fairleigh Dickinson (1-1), which shot 48 of 79 (60.8 percent) from the field. Darian Anderson had 14 points while Tyrone O'Garro and Ghassan Nehme each had 10. Florham started the game with an 8-2 run. The Knights answered with a 24-2 run, taking the lead for good on their way to a 68-point first half. Derek Leohner led the Devils with 17 points, making 4 of 6 from 3-point range. Jayson Hughes added 13 points.
